pecified time range. Below is the analysis:\n\n### Analysis Results\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_log_keys\": [\n    \"gc\",\n    \"context deadline exceeded\",\n    \"java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\",\n    \"DeadlineExceeded\",\n    \"HelperManager.install\",\n    \"Byteman\",\n    \"Transformer inserted trigger\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"High frequency of garbage collection (GC) related logs, rule triggering, and helper activation issues. Evidenced by 'AdService--gc-1749553853', 'HelperManager.install', and 'Transformer inserted trigger' associated with GCHelper.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Logs indicate rule executions triggering GC events, possible errors with helpers ('HelperManager.install'), and repeated logs of 'java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException'.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend\",\n      \"reason\": \"Dependent service (frontend) experiencing 'context deadline exceeded' errors, potentially due to unavailability or delayed responses from AdService.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Logs include: 'rpc error: code = DeadlineExceeded desc = context deadline exceeded' with associated request IDs and HTTP paths targeting AdService.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Details\n1. **AdService Diagnosis**:\n   - Frequent appearance of `AdService--gc-1749553853`, `HelperManager.install`, and `Transformer inserted trigger`.\n   - Issues observed with `java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException` possibly caused by instability during GC events.\n   - Multiple nodes (aiops-k8s-03, aiops-k8s-07, aiops-k8s-08) observed generating GC-related logs frequently.\n\n2. **Frontend Diagnosis**:\n   - Frontend service logs show \"failed to get ads: rpc error: code = DeadlineExceeded desc = context deadline exceeded.\"\n   - Requests targeted AdService resources, and failures observed in HTTP requests due to ads retrieval issues.\n\n### Conclusion\nThe key issue origin